This is, of course, hummus. And hummus is
something, oh my God.

00:09:51.050 --> 00:09:52.940
[Janna laughs]

00:09:52.940 --> 00:10:02.460
Ok. Hummus. Now, hummus is basically very,
very simple dish. It's chick peas, soaked

00:10:02.460 --> 00:10:10.750
and cooked, tahini, lemon juice, water, condiments.
It's popular all over the Middle East. Everybody

00:10:10.750 --> 00:10:16.300
has hummus for breakfast, maybe as a part
of mesa plate, but in Israel, hummus is actually,

00:10:16.300 --> 00:10:21.810
I think I would call it a religion. Definitely
cult food. People rarely make it at home.

00:10:21.810 --> 00:10:27.000
They usually go out to a restaurant. This
one is, for example, from a place called Hummus

00:10:27.000 --> 00:10:34.761
Said in Akko, one of the most famous hummus
places in Israel. And it's very male thing,

00:10:34.761 --> 00:10:40.770
you don't use knife and fork, you use, you
know, piece of very light, fluffy pita and

00:10:40.770 --> 00:10:41.770
you mop it up.

00:10:41.770 --> 00:10:47.940
And if you had real hummus, freshly made that
didn't spend any time in the refrigerator,

00:10:47.940 --> 00:10:53.860
you will know it's an amazing, amazing dish.
Otherwise, I know many Jewish people in the

00:10:53.860 --> 00:10:59.160
United States, know it as something you serve
at the bar mitzvah, and it's, it's, I mean,

00:10:59.160 --> 00:11:04.410
really nothing impressive. This is not real
hummus. Real hummus you make and you serve

00:11:04.410 --> 00:11:11.270
at once. It has to be warm because, you know
hummus in Hebrew is "himtza." Vinegar in Hebrew

00:11:11.270 --> 00:11:17.240
is "hometz." It's the same root and this is
not accidental. Hummus spoils very, very quickly,

00:11:17.240 --> 00:11:23.110
so to make industrial hummus, which what most
people in the States know as hummus, you have

00:11:23.110 --> 00:11:30.090
to stuff it with antioxidants, add citric
acids, all kinds of stuff that spoils the

00:11:30.090 --> 00:11:31.090
flavor.

00:11:31.090 --> 00:11:34.730
It's actually very easy to make hummus at
home. The recipes in my book, but you can

00:11:34.730 --> 00:11:40.900
find it anywhere and the secret is make it
and serve it. There is no other way and when

00:11:40.900 --> 00:11:48.670
it's good, it's really, really amazing; fluffy,
flavorful, and actually there was a research

00:11:48.670 --> 00:11:54.440
conducted lately that proves that eating hummus
actually releases endorphin in your mind.

00:11:54.440 --> 00:12:00.190
So, it's the ultimate make good, make feel
well food. So, let's see if I'll be able to

