00:19:16.960 --> 00:19:21.119
food that turned all Israeli favorite.

00:19:21.119 --> 00:19:29.820
And now we're moving on to the next interesting
ingredient that is maybe one single most important

00:19:29.820 --> 00:19:36.999
ingredient in modern Israeli cuisine, and
this is, of course, tahini. I have it here.

00:19:36.999 --> 00:19:42.309
And it's made from sesame. One hundred percent
ground sesame; nothing else. Nothing else

00:19:42.309 --> 00:19:49.440
should be there. Now, in Israel, we use it
for salads, for cooking, for dressing, for,

00:19:49.440 --> 00:19:55.730
even for pastry. In the States, I think it's
largely misunderstood and used usually only

00:19:55.730 --> 00:20:02.010
for hummus. I have to convince people to actually
make some use of it. In the end, if we have

